examples.en: We were put off by the speaker's preachy tone.
Glitches in the speaker's schedule caused some delays.
The crowd relaxed into laughter at the speaker's excellent joke.
The speaker's forceful words persuaded his opponent to climb down.
The students disagreed with the speaker's opinion and howled him down.
The speaker's discursive style made it difficult to understand his point.
The introduction highlighted the speaker's distinguished career in linguistics.
Most of the speaker's remarks were addressed to those with experience in the industry.
He imitated the speaker's manner to a fare-thee-well. *
The audience felt that the speaker's remarks hit pretty close to home. *
